WEBVTT

00:03.291 --> 00:05.083
♪ OHHH OHHH OHHH ♪

00:07.166 --> 00:09.000
(Pete) ELEANOR BERGEN.

00:09.041 --> 00:12.625
23 WEEKS IN, THE O.B. NOTICED
AN ABNORMALITY WITH THE BABY.

00:12.667 --> 00:15.792
SHE'S HERE TODAY FOR
A 3-D ULTRASOUND TO FOLLOW UP.

00:15.834 --> 00:18.417
WHOA.
I KNOW.

00:18.458 --> 00:22.125
WELL, THERE'S A BUILDUP
OF CEREBROSPINAL FLUID.
DOCTORS SPLIT
ON WHAT TO DO HERE.

00:22.166 --> 00:25.458
SOME SAY WAIT AS LONG
AS POSSIBLE TO TAKE THE BABY,

00:25.500 --> 00:28.667
THEN CLEAR IT ONCE IT'S OUT.
WELL, IF THE SWELLING CONTINUES,
THE BABY COULD HAVE

00:28.709 --> 00:31.125
SEVERE BRAIN DAMAGE AND POSSIBLY
RUPTURE THE MOTHER'S UTERUS.

00:31.166 --> 00:34.125
WELL, THAT'S THE OTHER CAMP.
THEY SAY DELIVER THE BABY NOW.

00:34.166 --> 00:37.667
23 WEEKS IS WAY TOO SOON.
OR TERMINATE.

00:37.709 --> 00:40.875
ELEANOR AND HER HUSBAND
DIDN'T KNOW WHAT TO DO,

00:40.917 --> 00:43.875
SO THEY CALLED ME, AND I
CALLED YOU TO BREAK THE TIE.

00:43.917 --> 00:45.875
THAT'S THE HUSBAND.
HI, RONALD.

00:45.917 --> 00:48.667
THIS IS THE DOCTOR
I WAS TELLING YOU ABOUT.
HI, ADDISON MONTGOMERY.

00:48.709 --> 00:51.041
THANK YOU SO MUCH FOR COMING.
MY WIFE AND I

00:51.083 --> 00:53.041
A LITTLE FREAKED,
A LOT FREAKED, ACTUALLY.

00:53.083 --> 00:54.917
WE LOOK AT THE SCAN,
AT THE BABY'S HEAD...

00:54.959 --> 00:57.417
AND SHE'S IN THERE PRAYING
THAT YOU'RE NOT GONNA TELL US

00:57.458 --> 01:01.125
TO GIVE UP.
LET'S, UH, TAKE A LOOK
AND WE'LL TALK AFTER, OKAY?

01:03.750 --> 01:05.125
(door opens)

01:09.959 --> 01:14.083
THIS IS MY WIFE...
ELEANOR.

01:20.083 --> 01:23.041
WELL, MAYBE THIS IS
MY PENANCE FOR PUSHING.

01:23.083 --> 01:26.208
EL...
I NEVER THOUGHT I'D HAVE
A CHILD UNTIL I MET RON,

01:26.250 --> 01:28.750
AND THEN WE JUST BOTH THOUGHT,
WHY NOT?

01:28.792 --> 01:31.458
WHY NOT TRY FOR EVERYTHING?
SO IT WAS A YEAR

01:31.500 --> 01:35.041
OF LOOKING FOR AN EGG DONOR,
THREE CYCLES OF I.V.F.

01:35.083 --> 01:39.125
NOW LOOK. (scoffs) JUST LOOK.
WHAT WERE WE THINKING?

01:39.166 --> 01:40.875
(Addison)
CONGENITAL HYDROCEPHALUS

01:40.917 --> 01:43.417
ISN'T NECESSARILY CORRELATED
WITH A MOTHER'S AGE.

01:43.458 --> 01:47.125
"NECESSARILY" BEING
THE OPERATIVE WORD.
IT'S A WASTE OF TIME
TO FEEL GUILTY.

01:47.166 --> 01:51.041
THIS IS OUR BABY.
THIS IS OUR CHANCE.
IF ELEANOR WERE TO
STAY HERE AND BE MONITORED,

01:51.083 --> 01:53.750
WOULD IT BE SAFE FOR HER TO
CONTINUE WITH THE PREGNANCY?

01:53.792 --> 01:55.875
I WOULDN'T, BUT THERE
COULD BE ANOTHER OPTION.

01:55.917 --> 01:58.041
I MIGHT BE ABLE TO DO
WHAT'S CALLED

01:58.083 --> 01:59.959
AN IN-UTERO
INTRACRANIAL SEPTOSTOMY.

02:00.000 --> 02:02.000
MEANING I'D GO IN
THROUGH THE UTERUS

02:02.041 --> 02:03.542
AND INTO THE BABY'S BRAIN,

02:03.583 --> 02:06.458
CREATE A HOLE
BETWEEN THE VENTRICLES.

02:06.500 --> 02:08.542
THAT WOULD DRAIN
SOME OF THE FLUID

02:08.583 --> 02:12.041
AND RELIEVE THE PRESSURE.
BRAIN SURGERY
WHILE THE BABY'S INSIDE ME?

02:12.083 --> 02:14.083
IS THAT... SAFE?

02:14.125 --> 02:18.125
HE MEANS, IS IT SAFE
FOR A WOMAN MY AGE?

02:18.166 --> 02:19.959
(Naomi) MAYA.

02:20.000 --> 02:22.959
I'M LEAVING NOW
IF YOU WANT A RIDE TO SCHOOL.

02:23.000 --> 02:24.333
I'LL CATCH THE BUS.

02:24.375 --> 02:26.583
ALL RIGHT. SIT NEAR
THE EMERGENCY EXIT.

02:26.625 --> 02:29.083
LOVE YOU. BYE.

02:32.083 --> 02:34.625
OH... (whispers indistinctly)

02:42.041 --> 02:44.125
WHAT THE HELL IS THAT?

02:44.166 --> 02:46.959
UM... CLOTHES AND MAKEUP.

02:47.000 --> 02:49.333
AND YOU WERE JUST GONNA WAIT
UNTIL I LEFT

02:49.375 --> 02:52.041
SO YOU COULD GO TO SCHOOL
DRESSED LIKE THAT?
THIS IS HOW ALL GIRLS DRESS.

02:52.083 --> 02:54.583
NOT THIS GIRL.
YOU HAVE FIVE SECONDS

02:54.625 --> 02:57.750
TO GET UPSTAIRS, WASH YOUR FACE
AND PUT ON SOMETHING DECENT.

02:57.792 --> 03:01.041
WE'LL DISCUSS HOW LONG
YOU'RE GROUNDED LATER.
YOU'RE RUINING MY LIFE.

03:01.083 --> 03:04.000
WHAT DID YOU SAY?
EXCUSE ME. WHAT DID YOU SAY?

03:04.041 --> 03:06.083
NOTHING!

03:06.125 --> 03:08.083
(door slams)

03:08.125 --> 03:09.792
(elevator bell dings)

03:09.834 --> 03:11.458
SHE'S 60 YEARS OLD, ADDISON.

03:11.500 --> 03:14.458
THE RISKS OF MAJOR SURGERY--
STROKE, ARRHYTHMIA,

03:14.500 --> 03:17.041
GETTING HER OFF THE VENTILATOR--
THEY'RE ALL MUCH HIGHER.
IT'S STILL THE BEST OPTION.

03:17.083 --> 03:20.041
FOR THE BABY, MAYBE.
BUT NOT FOR ELEANOR.
IF WE TRY TO STRING THIS OUT

03:20.083 --> 03:22.041
AND BRING IT CLOSER
TO VIABILITY,

03:22.083 --> 03:25.041
IT IS NOT JUST THE BABY
THAT COULD BE IN TROUBLE, PETE.

03:25.083 --> 03:27.542
I MEAN, YOU SAW THE SCAN.

03:27.583 --> 03:31.333
SHE'S GOT, LIKE, A LITTLE
TIME BOMB IN HER UTERUS.
THEN WE SHOULD ADVISE THEM
TO TERMINATE AND TRY AGAIN.

03:31.375 --> 03:34.542
AND WHAT ARE THE ODDS
OF THAT HAPPENING?
THEY COULD USE A SURROGATE
OR ADOPT.

03:34.583 --> 03:37.041
YOU THINK SOMEBODY'S GONNA GIVE
A 60-YEAR-OLD WOMAN A BABY?

03:37.083 --> 03:39.417
YOU THINK ELEANOR'S
TOO OLD TO BE A PARENT?

03:39.458 --> 03:41.458
I THINK IT'S A LITTLE WEIRD

03:41.500 --> 03:43.625
TO INTRODUCE YOUR PROM DATE
TO YOUR 80-YEAR-OLD MOTHER.

03:43.667 --> 03:45.208
THAT'S ONE OF THE DOWNSIDES

03:45.250 --> 03:47.208
OF GETTING GOOD
AT FERTILITY TREATMENT.

03:47.250 --> 03:50.208
EVERYONE THINKS THEY SHOULD BE
ABLE TO HAVE THEIR OWN BABY,

03:50.250 --> 03:52.291
EVEN AT 60.
I DON'T KNOW.

03:52.333 --> 03:55.291
MAYBE THIS CHILD
JUST WASN'T MEANT TO BE.

03:55.333 --> 03:57.917
NOT MY B--NOT OUR--
NOT LUCAS.

03:57.959 --> 04:01.041
A PATIENT.
SHE'S 60 AND PREGNANT.
OH.

04:01.083 --> 04:03.041
WELL, IF SHE'S HAPPY SENDING
HER HUSBAND OUT

04:03.083 --> 04:05.500
FOR DENTURES AND DIAPERS,
THEN MORE POWER TO HER.

04:05.542 --> 04:07.583
YEAH, WELL,
THE HUSBAND'S 30.

04:07.625 --> 04:09.083
EVEN MORE POWER TO HER.

04:09.125 --> 04:12.000
NOW WAIT A MINUTE. WHEN PETE
WAS DATING YOUNGER WOMAN,

04:12.041 --> 04:14.333
YOU SAID IT WAS DISGUSTING.
DON'T BRING ME INTO THIS.

04:14.375 --> 04:17.333
NO, I'M JUST POINTING OUT THAT
VIOLET HAS A DOUBLE STANDARD.

04:17.375 --> 04:20.542
THERE IS A STIGMA ATTACHED
TO DATING OLDER WOMEN,

04:20.583 --> 04:23.709
SO I FIGURE IF A GUY DOES, HE'S
IN IT FOR THE RIGHT REASONS.

04:26.667 --> 04:28.125
OH, RIGHT. LUNCH.

04:28.166 --> 04:31.750
UH... PETE, THIS IS
MY FATHER, THE CAPTAIN.

04:31.792 --> 04:33.542
NICE TO MEET YOU.
YEAH.

04:33.583 --> 04:36.000
AND, UH, THIS IS, UH...

04:39.583 --> 04:41.333
OH, HI. SORRY.

04:41.375 --> 04:44.041
NOT AT ALL.

04:44.083 --> 04:47.041
SEE?
IT IS DISGUSTING.

04:47.083 --> 04:48.792
COME ON, LET'S GO.

04:52.208 --> 04:56.083
I ALMOST KILLED
YOUR CHILD TODAY.
OH, SO TODAY SHE'S MY CHILD.

04:56.125 --> 04:59.166
NO, YOU WOULD'VE HAD TO
BURY HER BODY IN SECRET

04:59.208 --> 05:02.000
TO KEEP ME FROM GOING TO JAIL.
OKAY, WHAT'D SHE DO?

05:02.041 --> 05:04.041
SHE TRIED TO
SNEAK OUT OF THE HOUSE

05:04.083 --> 05:07.041
DRESSED UP LIKE SOME
25-YEAR-OLD I DON'T KNOW WHAT.

05:07.083 --> 05:09.542
(laughs) YOU REMEMBER WHEN SHE
USED TO PUT ON YOUR LIPSTICK--

05:09.583 --> 05:13.083
SAM, SHE'S NOT 4,
AND THIS IS NOT SWEET.
OH, COME ON NOW, NAI.

05:13.125 --> 05:16.041
DON'T "NAI" ME. SHE WAS TRYING
TO PULL ONE OVER ON ME.

05:16.083 --> 05:18.583
AND THEN WHEN I CALLED HER
ON IT, SHE STOMPED AWAY

05:18.625 --> 05:21.625
AND SLAMMED THE DOOR,
IN MY HOUSE.
YOU SAID YOU
ALMOST KILLED HER, RIGHT?

05:21.667 --> 05:23.625
I AM NOT GONNA LET
OUR DAUGHTER TURN INTO

05:23.667 --> 05:25.625
ONE OF THOSE SNOT-NOSED
PRIVATE SCHOOL KIDS

05:25.667 --> 05:28.625
WHO JUST THINKS THAT THEY CAN
DO WHATEVER THEY WANT.
THAT IS NOT MAYA.

05:28.667 --> 05:31.625
WELL, APPARENTLY,
WE DON'T KNOW MAYA.
WELL, TRY NOT TO GET
YOURSELF ALL WORKED UP.

05:31.667 --> 05:33.834
SAM, SHE IS
HIDING THINGS FROM ME,

05:33.875 --> 05:35.917
WHICH MEANS
SHE DOESN'T TRUST ME

05:35.959 --> 05:38.417
OR SHE IS DOING SOMETHING
THAT SHE KNOWS IS WRONG.

05:38.458 --> 05:40.417
AND YOU THINK THIS IS
MORE THAN HER

05:40.458 --> 05:43.041
JUST PUTTING ON
SOME SKIMPY CLOTHES?
I DON'T KNOW.

05:43.083 --> 05:46.041
I DON'T KNOW, BUT I'M GONNA
TURN HER ROOM UPSIDE DOWN

05:46.083 --> 05:49.792
UNTIL I FIGURE OUT
EXACTLY WHAT'S GOING ON.
(sighs)

05:49.834 --> 05:52.166
(coos)
WELL, UH, RUTHIE LOOKS FINE.
HOW ARE YOU DOING?

05:52.208 --> 05:55.250
GREAT.
YEAH, YOU GOT
THESE TWO LITTLE ONES

05:55.291 --> 05:58.041
AND 4 OTHERS AT HOME
UNDER, WHAT, 8,

05:58.083 --> 06:00.959
AND YOU'RE--
YOU'RE GREAT, HUH?
I'M VERY BLESSED.

06:01.000 --> 06:02.750
DOESN'T MEAN
YOU CAN'T COMPLAIN.

06:02.792 --> 06:06.000
TELL ME YOU'RE EXHAUSTED.
OH, I GAVE UP ON SLEEP
A LONG TIME AGO.

06:06.041 --> 06:08.500
I MEAN, YOU GOT
NO TIME TO YOURSELF OR...

06:11.250 --> 06:13.208
IT'S, UH, SHIMMON.

06:13.250 --> 06:16.166
YEAH, IT'S YOUR HUSBAND?
HE'S NOT...

06:16.208 --> 06:18.709
INTERESTED.

06:20.792 --> 06:23.333
OH, UH, OKAY.
WELL, THAT, UH, THAT HAPPENS.

06:23.375 --> 06:25.250
SOME MEN FEEL AWKWARD
WITH THEIR WIVES

06:25.291 --> 06:28.041
DURING OR SOMETIMES EVEN AFTER
PREGNANCY, BUT IT PASSES.

06:28.083 --> 06:31.041
DR. FREEDMAN, I SHOULDN'T BE
TALKING TO YOU ABOUT THIS.

06:31.083 --> 06:33.208
IT'S NOT PROPER.
IF THERE'S A PROBLEM--

06:33.250 --> 06:36.333
IT'S NOT PROPER, AND, UH,
I DON'T THINK YOU CAN HELP.

06:39.333 --> 06:41.417
I NEED YOUR HELP.

06:41.458 --> 06:43.417
IF YOU KNEW SOMEBODY
WAS ADMIRING YOU,

06:43.458 --> 06:45.041
SPECIFICALLY YOUR ASS,

06:45.083 --> 06:47.041
WOULD THAT
JUST BE FLATTERING,

06:47.083 --> 06:49.375
OR WOULD THAT
GET YOU AROUSED?

06:49.417 --> 06:51.000
WHO'S ADMIRING MY ASS?

06:51.041 --> 06:53.000
'CAUSE I THINK THAT WOULD BE
AROUSING, RIGHT?

06:53.041 --> 06:55.000
YEAH.
TO KNOW THAT SOMEBODY
RIGHT NEAR YOU

06:55.041 --> 06:57.041
IS THINKING ABOUT YOU
SEXUALLY?

06:57.083 --> 06:59.250
WAIT, WHO ARE WE
TALKING ABOUT, ME OR YOU?

06:59.291 --> 07:01.333
W-WE'RE TALKING ABOUT Y-YOU,
RIGHT?

07:01.375 --> 07:03.333
YOU ASKED ME TO HELP YOU
WITH SOMETHING?

07:03.375 --> 07:05.333
OH, YEAH. UM, A PATIENT.

07:05.375 --> 07:07.417
TWO MONTHS POSTPARTUM,
AND SHE'S CONCERNED

07:07.458 --> 07:09.750
'CAUSE HER HUSBAND
IS NOT INTERESTED IN SEX.

07:09.792 --> 07:11.750
OH, WELL, COULD BE
DEPRESSION, STRESS,

07:11.792 --> 07:13.125
PERFORMANCE ANXIETY.

07:13.166 --> 07:15.041
UNLESS IT'S VASCULAR DISEASE,
HYPERTHYROIDISM,

07:15.083 --> 07:16.625
IATROGENIC IMPOTENCE.

07:16.667 --> 07:18.834
FORGET WHERE
MY OFFICE IS, COOP,

07:18.875 --> 07:21.083
THE ONE WITH
ALL THE MARITAL AIDS

07:21.125 --> 07:24.250
AND BOOKS YOU SNEAK IN
TO LOOK AT DURING LUNCH?
NO, I WAS JUST--

07:24.291 --> 07:26.667
REFERRING A PATIENT TO VIOLET
YOU SHOULD BE REFERRING TO ME

07:26.709 --> 07:30.875
BECAUSE YOU'RE STILL MAD
AND PETTY.
PETTINESS ASIDE, THERE'S NO
REASON TO JUMP TO PHYSIOLOGY.

07:30.917 --> 07:32.917
I MEAN, SEX ISSUES,
MORE OFTEN THAN NOT,

07:32.959 --> 07:34.959
ARE ROOTED IN
EMOTIONAL DYSFUNCTIONS.

07:35.000 --> 07:38.166
YES.
ACTUALLY, WE'RE FINDING
MORE AND MORE

07:38.208 --> 07:41.166
THAT PROBLEMS IN THE BEDROOM
STEM FROM HORMONAL IMBALANCES,

07:41.208 --> 07:43.458
NERVE PROBLEMS, ALL KINDS
OF EQUIPMENT FAILURE.

07:43.500 --> 07:46.375
OKAY, YOU KNOW WHAT? I WOULD
LIKE TO SEE HER ALONE FIRST.

07:46.417 --> 07:48.667
I THOUGHT WE WERE
ONE BIG TEAM HERE AT O.W.G.

07:48.709 --> 07:51.792
OR IS THAT ONLY WHEN YOU WANT IN
ON OTHER PEOPLE'S PATIENTS?

07:54.083 --> 07:57.291
(indistinct conversations)

07:59.792 --> 08:01.917
SO HOW EXACTLY
DO YOU SEE THIS WORKING?

08:01.959 --> 08:04.917
HAVING AN AWKWARD LUNCH
TOGETHER EVERY FEW DAYS

08:04.959 --> 08:07.500
THAT IT TAKES YOU THREE
VODKA TONICS TO GET THROUGH

08:07.542 --> 08:10.542
AND ME A HALF A BOTTLE OF WINE
AT NIGHT TO FORGET?

08:10.583 --> 08:12.834
ADDISON, PLEASE.

08:12.875 --> 08:14.166
(clears throat)

08:14.208 --> 08:16.542
I ENJOYED
SEEING YOUR OFFICE.

08:16.583 --> 08:18.750
VIOLET'S ASS
OR THE WHOLE THING?

08:18.792 --> 08:22.125
I'D LIKE
TO SEE YOUR HOUSE.

08:22.166 --> 08:25.041
SO WE COULD SIT THERE
AND STARE AT EACH OTHER,

08:25.083 --> 08:27.417
SEE WHO BLINKS FIRST
WITHOUT EVEN A WAITER

08:27.458 --> 08:29.041
TO BREAK THE TENSION?

08:29.083 --> 08:30.625
(chuckles) NO.

08:32.542 --> 08:34.834
YOU WORKING ON
ANYTHING INTERESTING?

08:34.875 --> 08:36.208
(chuckles) I'M JUST...

08:36.250 --> 08:39.041
I'M TRYING, ADDISON.

08:39.083 --> 08:41.041
(clears throat)

08:43.083 --> 08:47.959
I MIGHT BE DOING AN IN-UTERO
INTRACRANIAL SEPTOSTOMY.

08:48.000 --> 08:49.166
REALLY?

08:50.709 --> 08:52.667
TRICK THERE IS GETTING
A GOOD ANGLE

08:52.709 --> 08:55.000
ON THE FORAMEN OF MONRO.

08:55.041 --> 08:56.166
RIGHT.

08:56.208 --> 08:59.041
AND THEN FINDING THE AVASCULAR
PLANE OF THE SEPTUM.

08:59.083 --> 09:01.583
YES. YEAH.

09:04.834 --> 09:06.792
SO WOULD YOU GO

09:06.834 --> 09:10.917
TO THE CONTRALATERAL
VENTRICLE FIRST?

09:12.250 --> 09:15.875
(Maya laughs)

09:15.917 --> 09:19.083
MOM.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HOME?

09:24.125 --> 09:29.000
I DON'T KNOW
WHO YOU ARE...

09:29.041 --> 09:31.208
BUT YOU SHOULD LEAVE.

09:31.250 --> 09:33.000
YES, MA'AM.

09:37.083 --> 09:39.458
(door opens)
MOM?

09:39.500 --> 09:41.041
DON'T...
(door closes)

09:41.083 --> 09:43.917
TALK.

09:43.959 --> 09:45.250
ONE...

09:45.291 --> 09:46.375
TWO...

09:46.417 --> 09:48.375
MOM, WHAT ARE YOU
GONNA DO?

09:48.417 --> 09:50.417
THREE... FOUR...

09:50.458 --> 09:52.458
MOM,
WHY ARE YOU COUNTING?

09:52.500 --> 09:53.750
FIVE...

09:53.792 --> 09:56.041
I AM TRYING
TO CALM MYSELF DOWN.

09:56.083 --> 09:57.917
SIX...

09:57.959 --> 09:59.041
SEVEN...

09:59.083 --> 10:01.041
IT'S NOT WORKING.
MOM--

10:01.083 --> 10:02.542
CALL YOUR FATHER.

10:02.583 --> 10:05.500
TELL HIM TO COME HERE NOW
AND SAVE YOUR LIFE.

10:09.083 --> 10:12.041
IT'S NOT THE FIRST TIME
SHIMMON HASN'T BEEN INTERESTED

10:12.083 --> 10:14.750
AFTER WE'VE HAD A BABY, BUT IT'S
LASTING LONGER THIS TIME.

10:14.792 --> 10:16.667
AND I STARTED THINKING...

10:16.709 --> 10:19.083
DOES YOUR HUSBAND F--
HOW OFTEN DO YOU
AND YOUR HUSBAND...

10:21.083 --> 10:23.375
OKAY, WELL, OTHER THAN
THE LACK OF INTEREST,

10:23.417 --> 10:26.125
HAVE YOU NOTICED ANYTHING ELSE
DIFFERENT ABOUT YOUR HUSBAND?

10:26.166 --> 10:28.458
WELL, LIKE WHAT?
IS HE EMOTIONALLY DISTANT?

10:28.500 --> 10:30.709
NOT AT ALL.
SHIMMON'S WONDERFUL.

10:30.750 --> 10:33.542
OH. OH, GOOD.
WELL, HAVE YOU NOTICED--

10:33.583 --> 10:36.458
ANY PHYSICAL CHANGES?
WELL, HE HASN'T BEEN
SLEEPING WELL,

10:36.500 --> 10:39.583
SO HE'S ALWAYS UP POKING AROUND
THE FRIDGE WITH WEIRD CRAVINGS.

10:39.625 --> 10:42.250
AND, WELL,
MAYBE I'M IMAGINING IT,

10:42.291 --> 10:45.041
BUT UP HERE...
GETTING A LITTLE FLABBY?

10:45.083 --> 10:47.792
IT'S THE COUVADE.
WHAT'S THAT?

10:47.834 --> 10:49.583
WELL, SOMETIMES
A WOMAN'S PREGNANCY

10:49.625 --> 10:51.583
CAUSES CHANGES
IN HER PARTNER'S HORMONES.

10:51.625 --> 10:53.583
HIS TESTOSTERONE GETS
CONVERTED TO ESTROGEN.

10:53.625 --> 10:56.166
IT'S A SYMPATHETIC REACTION,
SO HIS SYMPTOMS MIMIC YOURS.

10:56.208 --> 10:58.583
BUT IT'S EASILY TREATABLE--
COGNITIVE BEHAVIORAL THERAPY--

10:58.625 --> 11:00.875
ANDROGEN SUPPLEMENTATION.

11:00.917 --> 11:04.417
EITHER WAY, WE CAN HELP YOU GET
SHIMMON CHARGED RIGHT BACK UP.

11:04.458 --> 11:07.000
I'M SORRY. MAYBE I'M NOT
BEING CLEAR.

11:07.041 --> 11:10.166
THAT'S NOT WHAT I WANT AT ALL.
I LOVE MY HUSBAND.

11:10.208 --> 11:12.166
I LOVE BEING INTIMATE WITH HIM.

11:12.208 --> 11:14.417
BUT I CAN'T HAVE HIM
CHARGED BACK UP.

11:14.458 --> 11:17.500
I THOUGHT YOU WANTED
HELP WITH YOUR SEX LIFE.

11:17.542 --> 11:20.291
WE HAVE SIX KIDS
WHO I ADORE.

11:20.333 --> 11:22.041
BUT IF I HAVE TO RAISE

11:22.083 --> 11:25.583
OR SHIMMON HAS TO PROVIDE
FOR ANY MORE...

11:25.625 --> 11:27.917
WE CAN'T USE BIRTH CONTROL,

11:27.959 --> 11:31.208
BUT WE CAN'T HAVE MORE KIDS.

11:31.250 --> 11:33.208
SO THIS COUVADE,

11:33.250 --> 11:37.667
IS THERE ANY WAY TO
KEEP IT GOING PERMANENTLY?

11:37.709 --> 11:39.667
SHE WANTS YOU
TO KEEP HIM TAMED,

11:39.709 --> 11:42.125
AND YOU'RE OKAY
WITH THAT?
WELL, PEOPLE HAVE

11:42.166 --> 11:43.959
MEANINGFUL RELATIONSHIPS
WITHOUT HAVING SEX.

11:44.000 --> 11:45.959
AND YET, WHEN THEY'RE NOT
HAVING IT,

11:46.000 --> 11:48.333
IT'S USUALLY A SIGN THAT
THERE'S A PROBLEM, ISN'T IT?

11:48.375 --> 11:50.959
YOU ASKED ME
TO HELP, COOPER.
NO, ACTUALLY,
I ASKED VIOLET TO HELP.

11:51.000 --> 11:53.333
AND I DON'T THINK THAT WHAT
RACHEL NEEDS RIGHT NOW

11:53.375 --> 11:55.333
IS FOR YOU
TO BRING HER BACK IN

11:55.375 --> 11:58.041
AND START TOSSING AROUND WORDS
LIKE "ORAL" AND "ANAL."
WELL, PERSONALLY,

11:58.083 --> 12:00.041
I DON'T THINK RACHEL NEEDS
TO GIVE UP SEX AT ALL.

12:00.083 --> 12:02.125
I MEAN, WHY SHOULD A WOMAN

12:02.166 --> 12:04.375
WHO'S FEELING SOMETHING
NOT ACT ON IT?

12:04.417 --> 12:07.041
NO MATTER HOW DEEPLY
SHE TRIES TO BURY HER FEELINGS,

12:07.083 --> 12:09.166
EVENTUALLY, THEY'RE GONNA
COME BACK, RIGHT?

12:09.208 --> 12:11.792
I THINK WE NEED TO
CONVINCE HER THAT IT'S OKAY

12:11.834 --> 12:15.041
TO USE BIRTH CONTROL.
WELL, I AGREE, BUT I DON'T
THINK SHE'S GOING THERE.

12:15.083 --> 12:18.000
I THINK WE'RE MISSING
A MAJOR PART OF THIS EQUATION.

12:18.041 --> 12:20.417
SEX... GUY INVOLVED.

12:20.458 --> 12:23.166
OR AT LEAST
THERE'S SUPPOSED TO BE.
YOU KNOW, HE'S RIGHT.

12:23.208 --> 12:26.250
WE SHOULD GET SHIMMON TO HELP.
BUT IF RACHEL
WON'T TALK TO A MAN,

12:26.291 --> 12:30.041
WOULD SHIMMON
TALK TO A WOMAN?

12:30.083 --> 12:31.625
(elevator bell dings)

12:31.667 --> 12:34.625
WELL, THEN EVEN IF THE BUILDUP
OF C.S.F. IS SIGNIFICANT,

12:34.667 --> 12:37.083
YOU CAN STILL GET
COMPLETE RESOLUTION.
IDEALLY, YES.

12:37.125 --> 12:39.041
UH...

12:39.083 --> 12:41.667
SO...
I HAVE A PATIENT,

12:41.709 --> 12:44.667
AND, UM, THEN I HAVE TO GO
TO THE HOSPITAL AFTER THAT.

12:44.709 --> 12:47.667
SO THANK YOU FOR LUNCH.

12:47.709 --> 12:49.458
OKAY.

12:52.125 --> 12:55.250
OH, HELLO.

12:55.291 --> 12:57.667
DR. MONTGOMERY.

12:57.709 --> 12:59.458
W--CAPTAIN.

13:01.959 --> 13:04.208
CAPTAIN.

13:04.250 --> 13:05.667
(chuckles)

13:07.083 --> 13:09.041
(Naomi) SHE WAS HERE

13:09.083 --> 13:12.875
DITCHING SCHOOL
ON HER BACK WITH SOME BOY.
HIS NAME IS DINK.

13:12.917 --> 13:15.875
YOU TOLD ME THAT YOU TWO
WERE JUST FRIENDS.
WAIT A MINUTE. WAIT.

13:15.917 --> 13:18.041
WHAT, WHAT, YOU--
YOU KNEW ABOUT THIS DINK?

13:18.083 --> 13:21.000
UH, NOT--NOT MUCH.
I-I KNOW THAT SHE LIKES HIM

13:21.041 --> 13:23.000
AND THAT HE'S IN THE BAND.

13:23.041 --> 13:24.667
HE'S IN A BAND, DAD.

13:24.709 --> 13:28.041
YOU TOLD ME
HE WAS IN THE BAND.

13:28.083 --> 13:30.959
(sighs) YOU TWO AREN'T...
HAVING SEX?

13:31.000 --> 13:33.583
NO!
SO YOU SAY. HOW ARE WE
SUPPOSED TO TRUST YOU, MAYA,

13:33.625 --> 13:36.583
WHEN YOU GO AND YOU DO
SOMETHING LIKE THIS

13:36.625 --> 13:38.709
AND YOU SHOW
SUCH POOR JUDGMENT?

13:38.750 --> 13:42.041
SO HAVING A BOYFRIEND
COUNTS AS POOR JUDGMENT?
YES. DID I SAY YOU COULD HAVE
A BOYFRIEND?

13:42.083 --> 13:44.166
DID I SAY
YOU COULD TALK TO BOYS?

13:44.208 --> 13:47.333
DID I SAY YOU COULD EVEN
BE AROUND A BOY?
OKAY, L--CALM DOWN.

13:47.375 --> 13:50.041
ALL RIGHT, LET'S JUST TRY
TO DISCUSS THIS RATIONALLY.
THAT'S FINE WITH ME.

13:50.083 --> 13:52.291
MOM IS THE ONE THAT'S
GETTING ALL WORKED UP.

13:52.333 --> 13:54.083
MAYA.

13:54.125 --> 13:57.041
MAYBE IF YOU HAD
A BOYFRIEND...
(gasps)

13:57.083 --> 13:59.834
WHAT? I WILL--I-I WILL KILL
THIS CHILD, SAM.
DON'T--NO, SHE--

13:59.875 --> 14:02.542
YOU--YOU BETTER GO UPSTAIRS
AND PACK A BAG.

14:02.583 --> 14:06.000
WHAT?
GO UPSTAIRS AND PACK
A BAG... (whispers) NOW.

14:12.959 --> 14:14.542
OKAY, DON'T WORRY.

14:14.583 --> 14:16.583
ALL RIGHT? I-I GOT THIS.

14:16.625 --> 14:19.583
UM, I'LL BRING HER OVER TO
MY HOUSE FOR A COUPLE OF DAYS.

14:19.625 --> 14:22.041
YOU'VE BEEN DOING ALL
THE PARENTING. IT'S MY TURN.

14:22.083 --> 14:24.000
THANK YOU.
I-I-I GOT THIS.

14:24.041 --> 14:26.125
YEAH,
YOU BETTER HAVE IT, SAM.

14:26.166 --> 14:29.542
THIS IS OUR CHILD.

14:29.583 --> 14:32.875
WHAT'S BRADYCARDIA?
IT MEANS THAT THE BABY'S
HEART RATE HAS SLOWED DOWN.

14:32.917 --> 14:35.000
NOBODY SAID ANYTHING
ABOUT THE HEART.

14:35.041 --> 14:38.041
IT'S A SIDE EFFECT
OF INCREASED CRANIAL PRESSURE.

14:38.083 --> 14:40.125
HOW DANGEROUS IS IT?

14:40.166 --> 14:43.041
(printer whirring)

14:43.083 --> 14:46.750
(paper rustling)

14:46.792 --> 14:49.458
(monitor beeping rhythmically)

14:49.500 --> 14:52.500
YOUR BABY ISN'T GOING
TO MAKE IT TO VIABILITY.

14:52.542 --> 14:55.792
WE EITHER NEED TO PERFORM
THE SEPTOSTOMY

14:55.834 --> 14:58.417
OR TERMINATE THE PREGNANCY.

14:58.458 --> 15:00.875
I'M SORRY.

15:00.917 --> 15:03.417
I'M WORRIED ABOUT YOU.

15:05.083 --> 15:07.500
LET'S JUST WORRY
ABOUT THE BABY.

15:07.542 --> 15:11.166
HOW SOON CAN YOU OPERATE?

15:11.208 --> 15:13.583
(Blue Roses' "Doubtful Comforts"
playing)

15:13.625 --> 15:16.000
I SHOULD DO THIS
MORE OFTEN.

15:19.625 --> 15:21.291
♪ WHEN YOU... ♪

15:21.333 --> 15:23.125
ANYTIME.

15:23.166 --> 15:27.208
♪ COME HOME TONIGHT ♪

15:27.250 --> 15:31.041
♪ MY LOVE ♪

15:31.083 --> 15:32.959
MM. I'M SORRY.

15:33.000 --> 15:36.041
I CAN'T. I CAN'T.
YOU DON'T NEED
TO SAY ANYTHING.

15:36.083 --> 15:39.083
IT'S JUST BEEN A LONG TIME,
YOU KNOW, SINCE I FELT THIS WAY.

15:39.125 --> 15:42.041
YOU KNOW, I'VE BEEN STUCK
IN MY HEAD FOR SO LONG,

15:42.083 --> 15:46.041
THE IDEA THAT I HAVE A BODY,
THAT I COULD BE TOUCHED...

15:46.083 --> 15:49.542
(voice breaks)
DO YOU MIND MY SCAR?

15:49.583 --> 15:51.667
NOT AT ALL.

15:51.709 --> 15:52.875
(whimpers)

15:52.917 --> 15:55.542
(cries)
I CAN'T LOOK AT IT.

15:55.583 --> 15:57.041
♪ WHERE THEY DON'T... ♪

15:57.083 --> 15:59.166
THEN DON'T.

15:59.208 --> 16:01.500
IT'LL FADE.

16:01.542 --> 16:03.166
AND IN THE MEANTIME,

16:03.208 --> 16:06.959
LET IT BE
A REMINDER THAT...

16:07.000 --> 16:11.041
YOU WENT THROUGH SOMETHING
NO ONE ELSE QUITE UNDERSTANDS

16:11.083 --> 16:13.959
AND SURVIVED...

16:14.000 --> 16:16.125
AND THAT YOU--
YOU EARNED THE RIGHT

16:16.166 --> 16:19.125
TO DO EXACTLY WHAT YOU WANT
FOR A WHILE,

16:19.166 --> 16:23.667
WHETHER IT'S THIS
OR... ANYTHING ELSE.

16:23.709 --> 16:26.667
♪ OOH ♪

16:26.709 --> 16:31.041
♪ OOH ♪

16:31.083 --> 16:34.333
I'M AFRAID ADDISON'S
GONNA HATE ME.

16:34.375 --> 16:37.041
YOU'LL BE IN GOOD COMPANY.
(laughs)

16:37.083 --> 16:40.083
(laughs)
DO YOU THINK THERE'S ANY WAY

16:40.125 --> 16:42.291
TO EXPLAIN IT TO HER
THAT SHE'D UNDERSTAND?

16:42.333 --> 16:44.291
EMOTIONAL DISCUSSIONS
ARE NOT OUR FORTE,

16:44.333 --> 16:46.083
SO I DON'T KNOW.

16:46.125 --> 16:48.291
THAT'S SAD.

16:48.333 --> 16:51.041
IT IS.

16:51.083 --> 16:54.000
I WAS ALWAYS...
WORKING, TRAVELING

16:54.041 --> 16:58.917
WHEN ADDISON HAD THIS OR THAT
GOING ON.

16:58.959 --> 17:02.166
NO ONE EVENT I MISSED
LOOMS LARGE,

17:02.208 --> 17:06.583
BUT IN THE AGGREGATE,
I SUPPOSE I...

17:06.625 --> 17:08.458
LOST TRACK OF HER,

17:08.500 --> 17:10.458
OF WHO SHE IS ANYWAY.

17:10.500 --> 17:12.875
BUT YOU'RE HERE NOW TRYING.

17:12.917 --> 17:16.125
I GUESS I SHOULD JUST
TRY HARDER.

17:16.166 --> 17:19.166
WELL, MAYBE IF YOU SAW HER
MORE HERE...

17:19.208 --> 17:22.041
IN HER ELEMENT...

17:22.083 --> 17:25.125
THAT MIGHT MAKE IT EASIER.

17:25.166 --> 17:27.792
IT MIGHT BE GOOD
FOR BOTH OF YOU.

17:27.834 --> 17:33.542
♪ OOH ♪

17:40.625 --> 17:42.375
MAYA'S BEING STUPID.

17:42.417 --> 17:45.041
WELL, SHE'S A TEENAGER.
IF YOU TAKE
HER SIDE IN THIS,

17:45.083 --> 17:48.041
I SWEAR, I WILL TAKE
MY CHOCOLATE AND I WILL LEAVE.
I AM NOT.

17:48.083 --> 17:50.583
I AM ON YOUR SIDE, NAI...
FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH.

17:50.625 --> 17:53.041
I MEAN, HONESTLY, YOU'D BE
HARD-PRESSED TO FIND SOMEONE

17:53.083 --> 17:56.041
WHO KNOWS LESS ABOUT FUNCTIONAL
PARENT-CHILD RELATIONSHIPS.

17:56.083 --> 17:58.917
WHAT, IS THE CAPTAIN THAT BAD?
HE SAYS HE WANTS
TO SPEND TIME WITH ME,

17:58.959 --> 18:01.041
BUT HE DOESN'T KNOW HOW
TO SPEND TIME WITH ME.

18:01.083 --> 18:03.792
WE TALKED ABOUT SURGERY.
HE LECTURES, AND I PRETEND

18:03.834 --> 18:07.041
TO NOT ALREADY KNOW
WHAT HE'S TELLING ME.

18:07.083 --> 18:10.041
I SHOULD JUST SEND HIM HOME,
LET HIM AND BIZZY CLANK AROUND

18:10.083 --> 18:12.542
IN THAT EMPTY HOUSE
IN WASP-Y SILENCE.

18:12.583 --> 18:14.542
YEAH, WELL, SITTING AROUND
IN YOUR EMPTY HOUSE,

18:14.583 --> 18:17.834
YOU START TO HAVE DOUBTS.

18:17.875 --> 18:20.667
WILL YOU PLEASE TELL ME THAT
I AM DOING THE RIGHT THING?

18:20.709 --> 18:23.041
YOU ARE DOING
THE RIGHT THING, NAI.

18:23.083 --> 18:25.041
(knock on door)

18:25.083 --> 18:27.625
I DON'T MEAN TO DISTURB YOU.

18:27.667 --> 18:29.917
NAOMI.
CAPTAIN, HOW ARE YOU?

18:29.959 --> 18:31.959
I CAME TO ASK A FAVOR.

18:32.000 --> 18:35.041
I WAS HOPING
I COULD OBSERVE YOU

18:35.083 --> 18:37.041
PERFORM THE SEPTOSTOMY.

18:37.083 --> 18:40.208
YOU WANT TO WATCH...

18:40.250 --> 18:43.250
ME?
I'VE NEVER SEEN YOU WORK.

18:43.291 --> 18:46.875
I KNOW YOUR REPUTATION,
OF COURSE, BUT, UH...

18:46.917 --> 18:49.041
I'D LIKE TO SEE IT,
TO SEE... YOU.

18:49.083 --> 18:51.333
(mouth full) OKAY.

18:51.375 --> 18:53.667
IF IT'S NOT AN IMPOSITION--

18:53.709 --> 18:56.000
JUST TAKE YES AS AN ANSWER.

18:58.417 --> 19:01.583
LOOK, I WORK TWO JOBS
SIX DAYS A WEEK,

19:01.625 --> 19:03.792
AND RACHEL IS CONSUMED.

19:03.834 --> 19:05.792
SHE MAKES OUR HOME,

19:05.834 --> 19:08.792
SHE JUGGLES SCHOOLS AND DOCTORS
AND MEALS AND BIRTHDAYS--

19:08.834 --> 19:11.458
SO MANY THINGS,
I LOSE TRACK.

19:11.500 --> 19:15.709
EXACTLY, SO AT A CERTAIN POINT,
WHETHER IT'S 7 OR 9 OR 12 KIDS,

19:15.750 --> 19:18.041
DO YOU THINK
YOU'LL WANT TO STOP?

19:18.083 --> 19:20.917
THE TORAH TELLS US
"TO BE FRUITFUL AND MULTIPLY,"

19:20.959 --> 19:23.291
FILL THE EARTH
AND SUBDUE IT.

19:23.333 --> 19:26.083
WE INTERPRET THAT TO MEAN
THAT WE CAN'T DO ANYTHING

19:26.125 --> 19:29.041
TO TRY TO PREVENT A PREGNANCY.

19:29.083 --> 19:32.041
I LOVE MY WIFE.

19:32.083 --> 19:36.417
AND NEITHER ONE OF US WANTS TO
GIVE UP... YOU KNOW--

19:36.458 --> 19:38.417
WHAT IF
WE COULD FIND SOMETHING

19:38.458 --> 19:41.375
THAT WASN'T TECHNICALLY
BIRTH CONTROL?

19:41.417 --> 19:43.041
UH...

19:43.083 --> 19:45.834
WE HAVE CHOSEN TO BE FAITHFUL,
DR. FREEDMAN.

19:45.875 --> 19:47.542
WHO WOULD WE BE FOOLING?

19:49.542 --> 19:52.333
(footsteps approach)

19:54.417 --> 19:56.208
PEOPLE ARE UNPREDICTABLE.

19:56.250 --> 19:59.208
LOOK, ADDISON--
JUST WHEN YOU THINK
YOU KNOW SOMEONE,

19:59.250 --> 20:02.208
THEY GO AHEAD
AND DO SOMETHING NICE.
WAIT, WHAT?

20:02.250 --> 20:05.041
MY FATHER. HE WANTS TO
WATCH ME DO SURGERY.

20:05.083 --> 20:08.000
I MEAN, THE MAN NEVER MADE
A SINGLE PIANO RECITAL,

20:08.041 --> 20:10.834
TENNIS MATCH--
NOTHING MY WHOLE LIFE.

20:10.875 --> 20:13.000
AND SUDDENLY--
THAT'S--THAT'S GREAT.

20:13.041 --> 20:16.375
VIOLET, LOOK, I KNOW THAT
YOU THINK PEOPLE CAN CHANGE,

20:16.417 --> 20:19.625
BUT DO YOU REALLY THINK
THE CAPTAIN--

20:19.667 --> 20:21.166
(cell phone rings)

20:21.208 --> 20:22.375
(beep)

20:22.417 --> 20:24.041
HEY, PETE.

20:24.083 --> 20:25.792
YEAH, OF COURSE.

20:25.834 --> 20:28.667
I'LL BE RIGHT DOWN.
UH-HUH. OKAY.

20:34.083 --> 20:36.583
(exhales)
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

20:36.625 --> 20:39.041
NOTHING.
NOTHING IS WRONG WITH ME.

20:39.083 --> 20:41.709
I'M NORMAL. I JUST--I JUST
DID SOMETHING NORMAL.

20:41.750 --> 20:43.583
CONGRATULATIONS.

20:43.625 --> 20:46.041
NO, REALLY. I, UM...

20:46.083 --> 20:48.625
(chuckles)
I SLEPT WITH SOMEONE.

20:48.667 --> 20:51.583
I DIDN'T THINK I WOULD,
BUT THEN I DID.

20:51.625 --> 20:56.000
AND IT WAS... NORMAL. I DIDN'T
EVEN THINK I CARED ANYMORE,

20:56.041 --> 20:58.834
BUT THEN I SLEPT WITH
THE CAPTAIN, AND IT WAS

20:58.875 --> 21:00.917
THE MOST NORMAL THING
I'VE DONE SINCE THE ATTACK.

21:00.959 --> 21:03.959
DID I JUST SAY HIS NAME OUT
LOUD? BECAUSE I WAS THINKING IT,

21:04.000 --> 21:07.125
AND THEN I JUST--
YEAH, I SAID IT OUT LOUD.
SO ALL THAT ABOUT
GETTING YOUR NEEDS MET--

21:07.166 --> 21:09.125
NO, NO, NO.
THIS WAS NOT ABOUT SEX.

21:09.166 --> 21:12.041
IT WAS... IT WAS GOOD.

21:12.083 --> 21:13.667
EXCEPT FOR THE PART

21:13.709 --> 21:16.041
WHERE YOU COMMITTED ADULTERY
WITH YOUR FRIEND'S FATHER.

21:16.083 --> 21:18.041
(knock on door)

21:18.083 --> 21:20.000
WE NEED A RABBI.

21:21.667 --> 21:24.625
SHE'S 15 YEARS OLD, ALL RIGHT?
SHE'S BECOMING HER OWN PERSON.

21:24.667 --> 21:26.417
WE GOTTA GIVE HER ROOM.

21:26.458 --> 21:28.417
ROOM TO WHAT,
ROLL AROUND ON THE COUCH

21:28.458 --> 21:30.041
WITH SOME BOY NAMED DINK?

21:30.083 --> 21:32.041
WELL, MAYBE WE SHOULD
MEET HIM, YOU KNOW,

21:32.083 --> 21:34.709
SEE WHAT KIND OF A GUY HE IS.
HE'S THE KIND OF GUY

21:34.750 --> 21:37.375
WHO HAD HIS HANDS ALL OVER
YOUR DAUGHTER'S--
OH, HEY, HEY, HEY.

21:37.417 --> 21:40.291
HEY, DO YOU REMEMBER WHAT YOU
WERE LIKE WHEN YOU WERE HIS AGE?

21:40.333 --> 21:43.375
OH, YEAH, WELL, YOU'RE--
YOU'RE NOT A GOOD EXAMPLE,

21:43.417 --> 21:45.041
BUT THIS DINK PERSON,

21:45.083 --> 21:47.041
HE LOOKS LIKE A SCRUFFY
LITTLE HORMONE.

21:47.083 --> 21:50.000
OKAY, I WILL TALK TO HER
ABOUT HIM.

21:50.041 --> 21:51.917
TALKING'S GOOD,
BUT YELLING'S FINE, TOO.

21:51.959 --> 21:54.083
SHE'S GOTTA FEEL LIKE
SHE CAN TRUST US.

21:54.125 --> 21:56.750
SHE NEEDS TO KNOW
THAT SHE CANNOT CROSS US.

21:56.792 --> 21:58.750
WE'VE GOTTA
HOLD THE LINE, SAM.

21:58.792 --> 22:01.041
TOUGH BUT FAIR.

22:01.083 --> 22:04.041
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
WHEN IN DOUBT, YOU...

22:04.083 --> 22:06.750
CHANNEL ME.

22:06.792 --> 22:09.542
THAT'S WORKED OUT WELL.

22:11.083 --> 22:13.917
YOU NEED TO TALK HER
OUT OF IT, DR. MONTGOMERY.

22:13.959 --> 22:17.291
I KNOW WHAT WE SAID,
BUT... WHEN I LOOK AT YOU

22:17.333 --> 22:19.917
AND I THINK ABOUT
WHAT THEY'RE ABOUT TO DO...

22:19.959 --> 22:21.583
WE DON'T HAVE TO DO THIS.

22:21.625 --> 22:25.333
IF YOU WANT TO SAVE THE BABY,
ELEANOR HAS TO HAVE SURGERY.

22:25.375 --> 22:28.917
(Eleanor)
I'M SCARED, TOO, RONNIE.

22:28.959 --> 22:30.291
BUT THIS OUR BABY.

22:30.333 --> 22:33.792
OKAY, MAYBE IT'S NOT MY EGG,
BUT IT'S GOT YOUR D.N.A.

22:33.834 --> 22:36.083
HONEY, IT'S YOUR CHILD.

22:36.125 --> 22:38.041
IT'S NOT THAT I DON'T
LOVE IT. I DO.

22:38.083 --> 22:40.125
BUT RIGHT NOW...

22:40.166 --> 22:43.750
I LOVE YOU MORE.

22:43.792 --> 22:45.750
I CAN'T EVEN THINK
ABOUT LOSING YOU.

22:45.792 --> 22:48.542
BUT YOU WILL.

22:48.583 --> 22:50.750
WE'RE NEVER GONNA HAVE
THE KIND OF TIME

22:50.792 --> 22:53.041
THAT OTHER COUPLES
HAVE TOGETHER.

22:53.083 --> 22:57.125
AND AFTER I'M GONE,
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE THIS...

22:57.166 --> 22:59.625
TO REMEMBER WHAT WE HAD

22:59.667 --> 23:02.542
AND WHAT WE WERE TOGETHER.

23:02.583 --> 23:05.041
LOOK, I GET THAT YOU WANT
WHAT'S BEST FOR ELEANOR,

23:05.083 --> 23:08.000
BUT IF YOU DO WHAT'S BEST
FOR THE BABY,

23:08.041 --> 23:10.834
I THINK I CAN GIVE YOU BOTH.

23:10.875 --> 23:14.166
RONNIE, PLEASE.

23:16.709 --> 23:19.166
OKAY.

23:19.208 --> 23:20.792
OKAY.

23:20.834 --> 23:23.417
(inhales and exhales deeply)

23:29.667 --> 23:33.166
VIOLET SLEPT
WITH ADDISON'S FATHER.

23:33.208 --> 23:36.000
SHE...

23:36.041 --> 23:38.083
I THOUGHT YOU'D WANT TO KNOW.

23:38.125 --> 23:40.083
WHY WOULD SHE DO THAT?

23:40.125 --> 23:41.709
WHY WOULD SHE TELL YOU?

23:41.750 --> 23:43.709
SOME PEOPLE CAN TALK TO ME.

23:43.750 --> 23:46.083
OH.

23:46.125 --> 23:50.083
I'M TRYING TO TELL YOU THINGS,
LIKE YOU WANTED.

23:50.125 --> 23:52.625
GOSSIPING ABOUT
WHO'S SLEEPING WITH WHOM

23:52.667 --> 23:55.417
IS NOT WANT I WANTED.

23:55.458 --> 23:58.625
WHERE ARE WE, COOPER,

23:58.667 --> 24:00.792
YOU AND ME?

24:02.667 --> 24:05.083
I DON'T KNOW.

24:12.083 --> 24:13.750
OKAY, HOLD ON, BABY.

24:13.792 --> 24:15.542
SIT STILL.

24:15.583 --> 24:18.375
I WISH SHE COULD GIVE
THE BABY A PARALYTIC

24:18.417 --> 24:20.000
TO SLOW EVERYTHING DOWN.

24:20.041 --> 24:22.000
CAN'T BECAUSE OF
ELEANOR'S AGE.

24:22.041 --> 24:23.792
WELL, YOU COULD. I WOULD.

24:23.834 --> 24:26.959
(Pete) I'VE LEARNED...
DON'T SECOND GUESS HER.

24:27.000 --> 24:28.959
WELL, I-I DIDN'T MEAN TO,
BUT THAT'S NICE.

24:29.000 --> 24:31.333
YOU'RE--
YOU'RE BEING PROTECTIVE.

24:31.375 --> 24:34.000
I CAN ONLY IMAGINE
WHAT SHE'S SAID ABOUT ME.

24:34.041 --> 24:35.375
SHE HASN'T,

24:35.417 --> 24:38.000
NOT MUCH ANYWAY.

24:38.041 --> 24:40.250
ARE YOU TWO... CLOSE?

24:40.291 --> 24:42.709
WE ARE.

24:42.750 --> 24:44.959
UM, NOT LIKE THAT.
I'M WITH VIOLET.

24:45.000 --> 24:47.250
WELL, I WAS WITH VI--
WELL...

24:47.291 --> 24:50.375
WE RECENTLY HAD A BABY
TOGETHER, SO WE'RE...

24:50.417 --> 24:53.208
WELL, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT WE ARE.

24:53.250 --> 24:56.125
WELL...
OKAY, I'M IN AT...

24:56.166 --> 24:58.583
2 MILLIMETERS.

24:58.625 --> 25:01.000
GET READY TO INFLATE.

25:02.792 --> 25:05.208
